For and While Loops
Loop constructs within an application are a very common place to find vul-
nerabilities. Recognizing them within binaries is often a key part of auditing.
While it’s not really possible to absolutely distinguish different types of loops
from one another in compiled code, recognizing them functionally within
binaries is usually pretty simple. They are generally characterized by a back-
wards branch or jump that leads to a repeated section of code. The following
example illustrates a simple whileloop and its compiled representation.
